      "You didn't become an HR leader to hunt for people. You became one to build culture, protect your team, navigate compliance, and keep your organization stable. Yet somehow recruiting has become your second full-time job, and it is eating you alive.",
      "Here is the thing nobody says out loud: you are not bad at recruiting because you lack talent. You hate recruiting because recruiting is not HR work. It is sales work. And your job description never said you signed up to be a salesperson.",
      "## The Farmer vs the Hunter Conflict",
      "Think of HR like farming and recruiting like hunting. They are opposing activities that happen to involve people, but the skill sets could not be more different.",
      "Farming requires patience, nurturing, protection, and risk mitigation. You are tending to what exists, making sure your employees stay healthy, engaged, and productive.",
