      "When recruiting gets delegated to an HR team that does not have the bandwidth or the hunter's toolkit, these roles sit open for months. The hiring manager gets frustrated. The team steps in to cover the gap, burning themselves out. HR gets blamed for a weak pipeline.",
      "The outcome is predictable: hiring timelines stretch. Candidate quality drops because you are hiring the people who applied, not the people you actually need. Turnover increases because you settled. And HR burns out because they are failing at a job they were never trained to do.",
